# ============================================================

# .cursorrules ‚Äî NestJS + Next.js Monorepo (shadcn/ui)

# ============================================================

## PROJECT OVERVIEW

This is a monorepo containing:

- `apps/api` ‚Üí NestJS (backend REST API)
- `apps/web` ‚Üí Next.js App Router (frontend)
- `packages/` ‚Üí Shared types, utils, configs, UI lib

## MONOREPO TOOLING

- Package manager : pnpm workspaces
- Build system : Turborepo
- Language : TypeScript (strict mode) everywhere
- Linter : ESLint + Prettier (shared config in `packages/eslint-config`)
- Git hooks : Husky + lint-staged

---

## GENERAL RULES

- Always use **TypeScript**. Never use `any`; prefer `unknown` with type guards.
- Use **path aliases** (`@/`, `@api/`, `@web/`, `@repo/`) defined in each `tsconfig.json`.
- No barrel re-exports (`index.ts`) in deeply nested folders ‚Äî import directly.
- All async functions must have explicit return types.
- Prefer `const` over `let`; never use `var`.
- Avoid magic numbers ‚Äî use named constants or enums.
- **No Emojis or Emoticons in UI/API Responses**: Never use emojis or emoticons (e.g., üìä, üì¶, üõí, üí∞) in UI components, notifications, logs, or API response bodies. If icons are needed, always import and use professional vector icons from **`lucide-react`**.
- All environment variables must be validated with **Zod** at startup (both apps).
- Write self-documenting code; add JSDoc only for public API surfaces.
- Each feature must be **self-contained**: co-locate types, hooks, utils, tests next to the feature.

---

## NESTJS (apps/api)

### Architecture

- Follow **modular architecture**: one module per domain feature.
- Module structure per feature:
  ```
  src/
  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ modules/
      ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ <feature>/
          ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <feature>.module.ts
          ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <feature>.controller.ts
          ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <feature>.service.ts
          ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <feature>.repository.ts   # optional
          ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ dto/
          ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ create-<feature>.dto.ts
          ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ update-<feature>.dto.ts
          ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ entities/
          ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ <feature>.entity.ts
          ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ <feature>.spec.ts
  ```

### Controllers

- Keep controllers **thin**: only handle HTTP concerns (parsing, status codes, response shaping).
- Use **class-validator** + **class-transformer** on all DTOs.
- Always define explicit HTTP status codes with `@HttpCode()`.
- Use **guards** for auth, **interceptors** for logging/transform, **pipes** for validation.
- Never put business logic in controllers.

### Services

- Services own all **business logic**.
- Always **inject** dependencies via constructor (never use `new` directly).
- Make services testable: no static methods, no direct DB calls (delegate to repository).
- Use **custom exceptions** (`BadRequestException`, `NotFoundException`, etc.) with descriptive messages.

### DTOs

- Every DTO must use `class-validator` decorators (`@IsString()`, `@IsEmail()`, etc.).
- Use `@ApiProperty()` from `@nestjs/swagger` on every DTO field.
- Separate create/update DTOs; update DTOs use `PartialType(CreateDto)`.

### Database (TypeORM / Prisma)

- **Prisma preferred**. Schema in `apps/api/prisma/schema.prisma`.
- Never run raw queries unless absolutely necessary; document them with a comment explaining why.
- Use database **transactions** for operations that mutate multiple tables.
- Repository pattern: wrap Prisma client calls in a dedicated repository class per entity.

### Auth

- Use **JWT** (access + refresh token strategy) via `@nestjs/passport`.
- Store refresh tokens **hashed** in the DB.
- All protected routes use `@UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard)`.
- Role-based access via `@Roles()` decorator + `RolesGuard`.

### Error Handling

- Use a global **exception filter** (`AllExceptionsFilter`) for consistent error shape:
  ```json
  {
    "statusCode": 400,
    "message": "...",
    "error": "Bad Request",
    "timestamp": "..."
  }
  ```
- Log errors with context (request id, user id) using the NestJS `Logger`.

### Testing

- Unit tests: `*.spec.ts` beside the file under test.
- E2E tests: `test/` folder, use `supertest`.
- Mock external dependencies with `jest.fn()` or `@nestjs/testing` `createTestingModule`.
- Coverage target: 80 % minimum.

---

## NEXT.JS (apps/web)

### App Router Conventions

- Use **App Router** (`app/`) exclusively. No Pages Router.
- Default to **Server Components**; add `'use client'` only when needed (interactivity, browser APIs, hooks).
- `page.tsx` ‚Äî route page (server component)
- `layout.tsx` ‚Äî shared layout
- `loading.tsx` ‚Äî Suspense fallback
- `error.tsx` ‚Äî error boundary (must be client component)
- `not-found.tsx` ‚Äî 404 boundary
- `route.ts` ‚Äî API route handler

### Data Fetching

- Fetch data in **Server Components** using `fetch()` with Next.js cache options (`cache`, `next.revalidate`).
- Use **React Query / TanStack Query** for client-side mutations and real-time data.
- Never fetch data inside client components on mount if it can be done server-side.
- Use **Server Actions** for form submissions and mutations from server components.

### Folder Structure

```
apps/web/
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ src/
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ app/                    # App Router pages & layouts
    ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ (dashboard)/        # Route group
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ components/
    ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ ui/                 # shadcn/ui generated components (DO NOT edit manually)
    ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ <feature>/          # Feature-specific components
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ hooks/                  # Custom React hooks
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ lib/
    ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ api.ts              # API client (fetch wrapper)
    ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ utils.ts            # cn() and shared utils
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ stores/                 # Zustand stores
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ types/                  # Frontend-only types
```

### State Management

- Local UI state ‚Üí `useState` / `useReducer`.
- Global client state ‚Üí **Zustand** (one slice per domain, in `stores/`).
- Server state / caching ‚Üí **TanStack Query**.
- Form state ‚Üí **React Hook Form** + **Zod** resolver.
- Never use `useContext` for global state ‚Äî use Zustand.

---

## SHADCN/UI

### Installation & Setup

- Init with `npx shadcn@latest init` inside `apps/web`.
- Components live in `src/components/ui/` (auto-generated path).
- Config in `components.json` at `apps/web` root.

### Component Rules

- **NEVER manually edit** files inside `src/components/ui/` ‚Äî they are regenerated by the CLI.
- **Prefer component properties over raw className styling**: If a shadcn/ui or custom primitive component supports dedicated attributes/properties (e.g., `variant="secondary"`, `size="lg"` on Button), always use those properties instead of hardcoding equivalent classes inside a custom `className` (e.g., avoid manual padding, background colors, and border styles when existing properties cover the requirement). Use `className` primarily for layout positioning, sizing, and spacing (e.g., `w-full`, `mt-4`).
- Compose shadcn primitives in `src/components/<feature>/` for feature-specific variants.
- Wrap shadcn components with your own interface to encapsulate logic:

  ```tsx
  // ‚úÖ Good
  // src/components/feature/user-avatar.tsx
  import { Avatar, AvatarFallback, AvatarImage } from "@/components/ui/avatar";

  // ‚ùå Bad ‚Äî using shadcn primitives directly in page files everywhere
  ```

- Use the `cn()` utility from `@/lib/utils` for conditional class merging (not `clsx` or `classnames` directly).
- Always use **`cva` (class-variance-authority)** for creating component variants.

### Theming

- All colors defined as **CSS variables** in `globals.css` using shadcn's convention:
  ```css
  :root {
    --background: 0 0% 100%;
    --foreground: 222.2 84% 4.9%;
  }
  .dark {
    --background: 222.2 84% 4.9%;
    --foreground: 210 40% 98%;
  }
  ```
- Never hardcode Tailwind color classes (e.g., `bg-white`, `text-gray-900`) in components ‚Äî use semantic tokens (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`).
- Dark mode via `class` strategy (set on `<html>`), managed by `next-themes`.

### Forms

- Always use **React Hook Form** + `<Form>` from shadcn/ui + **Zod** schema:
  ```tsx
  const form = useForm<z.infer<typeof schema>>({
    resolver: zodResolver(schema),
    defaultValues: { ... },
  })
  ```
- Use `<FormField>`, `<FormItem>`, `<FormLabel>`, `<FormControl>`, `<FormMessage>` wrappers.
- Never use native `<form>` with uncontrolled inputs.

### Accessibility

- Every interactive component must have an accessible label (`aria-label`, `aria-labelledby`, or visible text).
- Use shadcn's built-in Radix UI primitives ‚Äî they handle keyboard navigation and ARIA roles.
- Color contrast must meet **WCAG AA** minimum.
- Use `sr-only` for visually hidden but screen-reader-accessible text.

